Pull up at a 4-way stop.
There seems to be some altercation, like a fender bender and one dude yelling at another.
It's rush hour and a line of cars is stopped behind me.
I can't drive through because they're fighting in the middle of the road.
Then one of them pulls out his semi-auto. Guns down the other guy. Then rages out.
Starts shooting into all the cars at the intersection.
Can't back up because there's a line of cars before me.
Can't go forward.
Watching him shooting all the drivers at the stop.
Knowing he'll shoot me in a second.
Wake up.

posts.com: I only had scary dreams as a kid. posts.name: Anonymous
posts.com:
>>892062636
Very rarely, but usually when i'm worrying about silly minor shit, my mind will give me a reality check with a dream so realistic it makes me quiet and subdued the whole day.

They started in my 20s, one was a bushwalk where i knew i was dreaming and marvelling at how vivid everything was, every leaf and twig and the grain of wood on flakes of bark. Then we're at a camp of old drunk dudes sitting around with mutilated bodies on the ground. One sruffy old fool is hauling the top half of a body by a chain then loops the chain over a tree branch to lift the body up. It's been gutted and the chain is hooked to the pelvis. The smell of blood is really strong.
No great terror, but the way all these people sit around apathetically as bodies are barbecued fills me with loathing.

Another one was a rainy, dark landscape full of wrecked vehicles like buses and helicopters, and they're all full of people squatting uncomfortably in them. As the sun comes up there's this one idiot walking around and i know he's extremely dangerous. Someone messes with him and as he knocks them over to peel their belly open i find i can actually look away in the dream, but still hear screams and tearing flesh.

Sure makes bills and arguments about parking spaces take their place with dandruff and bedfarts in importance.

I lived a whole life in a dream once. I met a girl, fell in love, had kids and a shitty job keeping the ovens at a bakery working. The dream ended when I was dying next to her in bed. It's fucked me up for a long fucking time. I still miss her and the kids we had in the dream despite them never actually existing. I'm married with kids now, but man if I don't miss my dream wife a maddening amount.

>>892062636
Last night i had a really strange dream. I was stopping on a road trip and ended up going inside this gigantic house where like 14-18 people lived. On the outside, It wasn't a mansion or even like a suburban house, it honestly looked like one of those "professional" business centers (townhouse style, not the indoor ones). On the inside it just looked like a labyrinth of lower-middle class style interior with a bunch of random rooms. one door would lead to the next and to the next. Very confusing floor plan. Didn't know the exact reason everyone was living there but I knew it was something sexual and that's all they did. They weren't having fun though, everyone there was absolutely miserable but it wasn't like they were being held against their will. I never got to have sex in the dream, I was referred to as "the baby" and I wasn't allowed to do anything sexual.

Nearly all of my "nightmares" are like this. Just weird fucking dreams.

>>892062636
The most disturbing dream i've ever had was in 2018. I was living in some sort of post-apocalyptic hell hole. The entire world had a red hue to it, everything was hot, and sparks were flying everywhere. Huge skyscrapers were crumbled and just left to rot. Thick black smoke was almost everywhere above everyone. everybody was forced to work and move gigantic steel objects by themselves for 18 hours per day under life threatening conditions. most people died on the job and they'd just get picked up and dumped somewhere. Nobody was allowed to have money, the government controlled every aspect of life. The government began administering an injection that altered people's minds to make them like the work they were doing. The injection forced a smile on everyone as they were working and they began to appreciate it thru the injection.

I wanted to emphasize that I had the dream in 2018. This dream alone convinced me to never take the covid vaccine.

There should be (on short footed horses) about a dime’s width of shoe behind the buttress (end of heel) and on the outside of the backend of the foot. The best way to describe this is to have the heel fit center of stock. Any time the foot grows over the shoe it needs to come off and be reset and properly fit. The back half of the foot is cartilage and will expand / contract.

There are a few reasons why the shoe isn’t a flat plate, though in certain situations it’s necessary and completely acceptable ie. hospital plates

The horseshoe should have zero contact with the sole. If it does, it’s called sole pressure, and constricts the circumflex artery and will sure enough lame the horse up the second it’s nailed on.

The frog is probably the most important part of the foot, and it is squishy. It’s the arrowhead shaped horny structure that more or less acts as the horse’s tennis shoe for traction and blood flow. It also sits directly under the center of articulation, aka the center of the pastern joint and coffin joint.

To help draw a picture, on a barefoot
>frog bears 33% of weight
>sole bears 33% of weight

The goal is to stay as close to light and natural as possible, as if the shoe weren’t there. Unless you’re fooling with a long footed horse or performance horse and want to manipulate motion.

>>892058879
Length is leverage. An average horse, like a quarter horse, Arab, TB, warm blood, etc. will have almost exactly 3 1/4 inches of foot. The golden means of measurement confirms this, that being the ratio of 1:1.618. Or easily enough, the hoofwall should be +/- 1/4” of a properly trimmed frog. Which is almost always 3-1/4”.

On a long footed horse, like your Tennessee walking horse or American saddlebred, you’re aiming for a particular motion that synchronized with a gait. Like racking, it’s a 4 beat gait and completely man made. Their legs move like bicycles. You take a 4 and 3/4” foot, add about 5 pounds of shoe and 3 inches of package to it (on the front end if it’s a pacer, back end if it’s a trotter) and you can achieve that motion. You have to manipulate the fuck out of the angles. A coffin bone should theoretically sit at 55 degrees and your trim should be right there with it. When a horse is long overdue it may end up going one way or the other, being really fucking high angled like 60 degrees or more, or completely low angled and end up in the 40s. Lots to explain, hard to really draw it out lmao. I stick with quarter horses.

>>892060024
High carbon steel is most common. Sometimes if you buy the right brand like Kerkhaert you can smell the sulfur burning off. Aluminum is common as well because it’s light and that is a lot more comfy in therapeutic and it also helps race horses be fast as fuuuuck boy.

You really want to shy away from soft metals, the ground will chew them to pieces. Especially sand, most especially wet sand or gravel. I can get 2 or 3 resets out of a pair of shoes in the right pasture. Sometimes I come back and the shoe is so worn down I can grab hold of it and twist it in half.

Copper coated nails are great because they are anti microbial and foul the foot less. Way too expensive for my taste. A regular box of nails costs me $6, copper coated or actual copper nails are $16-$25.

Wood clogs are still used today especially on foundered horses. Also in the modern era we even have acrylic and glue ons, it’s remarkable.
